
### Global `.gitignore` for Frontend & Backend

To handle both **Flutter (frontend)** and **FastAPI (backend)**, we can create a **global `.gitignore`** to exclude common files and directories for both environments. This will ensure that unnecessary or sensitive files (like temporary files, build directories, and Python-specific files) don't get committed to the repository.

#### **.gitignore** (global)

```gitignore
# General
*.log
*.env
*.sqlite3
*.db
*.pyc
*.pyo
__pycache__
*.bak
*.swp

# Backend - FastAPI / Python
# Virtual environments
venv/
env/
.venv/
.env/
# Python bytecode
*.pyc
*.pyo
__pycache__/
# MySQL files
*.sql
*.bak

# Frontend - Flutter
# Flutter specific
.flutter-plugins
.flutter-plugins-dependencies
.flutter-version
.idea/
.vscode/
*.iml

# Flutter build files
/build/
ios/Flutter/.last_build_id
ios/Pods/
ios/Runner.xcworkspace/

# Dart packages
.packages
pubspec.lock

# MacOS
.DS_Store

# IDE and editor configurations
.idea/
.vscode/
*.iml

# Operating system files
Thumbs.db
